  "text": "In this issue of Neurology ® , the research by Haley et al. [CITATION_1] meets the challenge for methodologic rigor by obtaining an epidemiologically derived sample of stroke survivor and caregiver dyads, following them for 36 months poststroke, and comparing them to a matched noncaregiving group. They used advanced statistical analyses to elucidate differences between caregiving and noncaregiving samples. As a result, Haley et al. substantially advance our understanding of poststroke care and its influence on caregiver health outcomes.",
